          <desc type="abstract" xml:id="abstract5146-1" xml:lang="en">[A] town in the Hindu-Kus̲h̲ north of the main range in a mountain valley lying 8,480 feet above sea level, through which one of the most important roads between the lands of the Oxus watershed and the Indus leads; the town is therefore naturally important as a commercial centre and was important in the middle ages as a fortress also. (Barthold/Allchin)</desc>
